A serving Metropolitan Police officer has been charged with sexually assaulting a colleague. Joseph Demir is alleged to have committed the offence while on duty. The incident is said to have happened on March 10, 2020, when the officer was a student at Hendon Training School. He was charged by post on Wednesday with sexual assault, a Met spokesperson said. Mr Demir is due to appear at Willesden Magistrates’ Court tomorrow. The offence was first reported on July 1, 2020. The PC is now attached to the North West Basic Command Unit. He has been taken off frontline policing duties and faces a disciplinary hearing after the court case. A spokesperson added: ‘PC Demir, who has been placed on restricted duties, was charged following an investigation by the Met’s Directorate of Professional Standards. ‘A misconduct hearing will take place once criminal proceedings have concluded.’ Get in touch with our news team by emailing us at webnews@metro.co.uk. For more stories like this, check our news page.